 Head of Service (HoS) Mr. Hakeem Muri-Okunola has assured public servants of improved welfare packages, as well as a conducive working environment, to ensure effective and efficient service delivery. Okunola, who spoke at a ministerial briefing to mark the first year anniversary of the Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu administration, held at JJT Park, Alausa, Ikeja, said in fulfilment of the current administration’s promise to strengthen institutional capacity of Ministries Department and Agencies, Governor Sanwo-Olu had granted approval for the procurement and allocation of official vehicles to the newly appointed permanent secretaries, principal officers in the public service as well as utility vehicles for use of Ministries Department and Agencies. He added that such procurement and allocation of vehicles included ministerial operational vehicles, departmental utility vehicles, specialised operation vehicles as well as bicycles and motorbikes for Central Business District (CBD) administration. “This is in line with the security and governance pillar of the T.H.E.M.E.S agenda of the current administration,” Okunola said.  The HoS said the Governor Sanwo-Olu administration has approved the conclusion of the 2020 promotion exercise in a manner that demonstrates understanding, compassion and emerging realities of the time. He said in recognition of the importance of a sustained availability of health care professionals at the health sector, the current administration has embarked on seamless automatic replacement procedure at the health sector and approved special allowances for health care professionals beyond the traditional hazard allowance. Okunola said as a clear demonstration of the commitment of the current administration to workers’ welfare, Governor Sanwo-Olu has approved the replacement of 35 old buses out of the fleet of 55 buses used in conveying civil servants to and from the secretariat, with 35 new Marcopolo Scania buses, adding that the fleet covers 44 routes across the five divisions of the state and the border towns of Akute and Mowe/Ibafo in Ogun State. He said Governor Sanwo-Olu has approved and released a whopping sum as housing loan subvention in fulfilment of his promise to prioritise workers welfare and has since disbursed loans to 1,372 members of staff, compared to what was achieved in 2018, adding that 88 eligible members of staff were issued letters of allocation of staff quarters, compared to 51 allotted in 2018.